Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a #large pot{} of salted water for the potatoes.

Halve the @Baby Potatoes{500%grams} widthways (quarter larger potatoes).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water, lower the heat to medium and cook until fork tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the #pot{}, off the heat.

Mix in a knob of @Butter{knob} and the @Dried Oregano{1%sachet}. Season to taste with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}. Set aside and cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, place your hand flat on top of the @Irish Chicken Breast{320%grams}.

Slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Repeat with the other breast(s).

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @Oil{to taste}.

When hot, add the chicken and season with salt and pepper.

Cook through, ~{3-6%minutes} each side. IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice the @Scallion{1}(thinly sliced).

Thinly slice the @Tomato{1}(thinly sliced).

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @Mayo{2%sachet} and scallion. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

When everything is almost ready, scatter the @Grated Cheese{50%grams} over the cut side of the @Brioche Buns{2} bases.

Pop the buns into the oven.

Cook until the cheese has started to melt, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Spread the mayo over the cut side of the bun lids.

Top the bun bases with slices of tomato and pan-fried chicken.

Spoon over the @Ballymaloe Tomato Relish{1%pot} then sandwich closed with the bun lid.

Serve the herby baby potatoes alongside.